data.chText: （表示两队或双方对阵）对，诉，对抗
data.enText: used to show that two teams or sides are against each other

data.chText: 决赛是法国队对巴西队。
data.enText: It is France versus Brazil in the final.

data.chText: 在州政府诉福特公司的案件中
data.enText: in the case of the State versus Ford

data.chText: （比较两种不同想法、选择等）与…相对，与…相比
data.enText: used to compare two different ideas, choices, etc.

data.chText: 那是她较好的就业前景与搬走并远离朋友的不便之间的矛盾。
data.enText: It was the promise of better job opportunities versus the inconvenience of moving away and leaving her friends.

means: (表示两队或双方对阵)对，诉，对抗
(比较两种不同想法、选择等)与…相对，与…相比

value.def: You use versus to indicate that two figures, ideas, or choices are opposed.

example.ex: Only 18.8% of the class of 1982 had some kind of diploma four years after high school, versus 45% of the class of 1972.
example.tran: 1982年那一届只有18.8% 的学生在中学毕业4年后获得了某种文凭，而1972年那一届这一比例是45％。
牛奶喂养与母乳喂养相比

value.def: Versus is used to indicate that two teams or people are competing against each other in a sporting event.

example.ex: Italy versus Japan is turning out to be a surprisingly well matched competition.
example.tran: 在意大利队对日本队的比赛中，双方竟出人意料地势均力敌。

example.ex: ...Greg Norman and Michael Campbell versus Retief Goosen and David Frost.
example.tran: 格雷格·诺曼和迈克尔·坎贝尔对阵雷蒂夫·戈森和戴维·弗罗斯特
